# Testing

Use this rule with `.ai/lifecycle/plan.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/test.md`, and `.ai/lifecycle/ship.md`.

{{> testCommands}}

## Unit & component

- Prefer **Testing Library** queries that reflect user-visible behavior (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`).
- Use `userEvent` over `fireEvent` when available.
- Co-locate tests as `*.test.ts(x)` / `*.spec.ts` consistent with repo convention.

## Mocking

- Mock network at the boundary (**MSW** or fetch mocks) instead of stubbing every component.

## E2E

{{#if hasPlaywright}}
- Prefer stable selectors (`getByRole`, `data-testid` only when necessary).
- Run against realistic auth states; reset storage between tests.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasCypress}}
- Avoid arbitrary waits; use assertions and retry-friendly matchers.
{{/if}}

## Storybook

{{#if hasStorybook}}
- Each complex component should have at least a **default** story + primary variants.
{{/if}}

## Coverage

- Cover critical user paths and edge cases; do not chase 100% line coverage blindly.

## Lifecycle Expectations

- Plan tests before implementation for non-trivial changes.
- Run targeted checks first, then broaden when shared components, routing, or data behavior changes.
- Include manual QA when automation does not cover accessibility, responsive layout, visual states, or adapter output.

## Must Avoid

- Tests that assert implementation details instead of user-visible behavior.
- Skipping error, empty, loading, disabled, and keyboard paths for interactive flows.
- Claiming adapter or generated-output checks passed without inspecting generated files.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Tests match the risk of the changed user flow.
- Skipped or missing checks are called out.
- Build, unit/component, E2E/manual, and accessibility checks are recorded when relevant.
